00:41:09.854 --> 00:41:13.258
- What the fuck are you doing?
- Didn't you want us to help you?

253
00:41:14.926 --> 00:41:17.562
- I want to see something.
- What?

254
00:41:17.829 --> 00:41:19.464
I'm not sure.

255
00:41:25.070 --> 00:41:26.738
I'm going up for a moment.

256
00:41:29.441 --> 00:41:31.109
Fuck! But what for?

257
00:41:31.910 --> 00:41:35.280
I think I've seen this building before.
it doesn't make any sense.

258
00:41:36.081 --> 00:41:38.383
But where do you think you've seen it?

259
00:41:38.950 --> 00:41:40.318
In Argentina.

260
00:41:50.628 --> 00:41:51.793
What are you doing?

261
00:41:51.863 --> 00:41:53.398
Andrea. who lives there?

262
00:41:55.100 --> 00:41:56.234
Nobody.

263
00:42:02.340 --> 00:42:06.845
STAIRS

264
00:42:58.797 --> 00:43:03.198
FIRST FLOOR

265
00:43:03.268 --> 00:43:05.437
Didn't you say nobody lives here?

266
00:43:07.172 --> 00:43:08.440
Just in case.

267
00:43:10.475 --> 00:43:11.910
Let's go.

268
00:43:34.466 --> 00:43:36.000
Wait for me here.

269
00:43:49.881 --> 00:43:51.082
I hate you.

270
00:43:57.789 --> 00:43:59.124
There is no power.

271
00:44:12.637 --> 00:44:14.305
Where are you going?

272
00:44:19.911 --> 00:44:21.212
Andrea. come here.

273
00:44:25.083 --> 00:44:26.484
Don't go away.

274
00:44:28.086 --> 00:44:29.420
There's someone there.

275
00:44:30.355 --> 00:44:31.489
Where?

276
00:44:32.056 --> 00:44:34.189
- There.
- Let's go. please.

277
00:44:34.259 --> 00:44:35.527
I don't see anything.

278
00:44:36.427 --> 00:44:39.197
It's him! Run. run!

279
00:44:40.431 --> 00:44:41.566
Run!

280
00:44:42.467 --> 00:44:46.337
- Andrea. Andrea. Andrea!
- Andrea. Andrea!

281
00:44:47.438 --> 00:44:50.205
Hello! Open up! Help!

282
00:44:50.275 --> 00:44:52.277
Please help!

283
00:44:52.810 --> 00:44:55.413
Please! Is there anybody there?

284
00:44:55.947 --> 00:44:58.046
- Please!
- Andrea!

285
00:44:58.116 --> 00:45:01.349
- Andrea. please!
- Please. Andrea. open up!

286
00:45:01.419 --> 00:45:04.522
- Andrea!
- Open the door! Open!

287
00:45:05.423 --> 00:45:06.758
Andrea. open up!

288
00:45:07.392 --> 00:45:08.526
Open!

289
00:45:09.594 --> 00:45:10.728
Andrea!

290
00:45:19.003 --> 00:45:20.371
<i>What happened in the house?</i>

291
00:45:21.506 --> 00:45:22.770
<i>When?</i>

292
00:45:22.840 --> 00:45:24.876
<i>On the night of the party.
what happened?</i>

293
00:45:25.677 --> 00:45:26.911
<i>Nothing.</i>

294
00:45:28.413 --> 00:45:31.616
<i>- You've been different since that day.
- You're crazy.</i>

295
00:45:32.383 --> 00:45:33.551
<i>Maybe.</i>

296
00:45:33.918 --> 00:45:35.283
<i>And you have bad memory.</i>

297
00:45:35.353 --> 00:45:37.288
<i>Why? What should I remember?</i>

298
00:45:37.689 --> 00:45:40.124
<i>You should remember the rules.</i>

299
00:45:41.259 --> 00:45:43.294
<i>Fuck the rules.</i>

300
00:45:43.695 --> 00:45:45.597
<i>Then there's only chaos.</i>

301
00:45:59.344 --> 00:46:00.545
Okay.

302
00:46:06.618 --> 00:46:07.885
Who's going to start?

303
00:46:11.222 --> 00:46:13.491
I don't think it was bad.

304
00:46:14.058 --> 00:46:15.890
In fact. I think I kind of liked it.

305
00:46:15.960 --> 00:46:18.830
"In fact. I think I kind of liked it."
What did you like?

306
00:46:19.664 --> 00:46:22.931
The story. The story's not bad.

307
00:46:23.001 --> 00:46:25.370
A few shots are...

308
00:46:25.937 --> 00:46:27.138
interesting.

309
00:46:28.606 --> 00:46:31.776
And it goes pretty fast.

310
00:46:33.211 --> 00:46:35.013
That's true.

311
00:46:36.114 --> 00:46:39.684
For two people in bed talking.

312
00:46:39.984 --> 00:46:42.287
the pace is okay.

313
00:46:44.656 --> 00:46:45.890
Who else?

314
00:46:46.424 --> 00:46:49.727
Yes. and then
there's the femme fatale theme.

315
00:46:50.261 --> 00:46:52.493
Alright. In what sense?

316
00:46:52.563 --> 00:46:56.868
I think Cami clearly wants to say
more about it. right?

317
00:46:57.869 --> 00:46:59.837
What does she want to tell us?

318
00:47:01.506 --> 00:47:04.309
I don't know.
she's much smarter than I am.

319
00:47:06.678 --> 00:47:09.113
I would have to see it again.
but I liked it.

320
00:47:11.149 --> 00:47:13.184
Do you want to add anything. Camila?

321
00:47:14.352 --> 00:47:15.987
No. nothing.

322
00:47:24.095 --> 00:47:25.263
Cami.

323
00:47:26.331 --> 00:47:27.332
Camila.

324
00:47:27.965 --> 00:47:29.300
How was it?

325
00:47:32.003 --> 00:47:33.705
I don't know. Fine.

326
00:47:35.907 --> 00:47:38.276
The short isn't good. you know that.

327
00:47:38.643 --> 00:47:41.209
The script wasn't great
and the shoot didn't help.

328
00:47:41.279 --> 00:47:45.083
You don't even know where it happens.
Where? Massachusetts?

329
00:47:46.351 --> 00:47:47.852
It's definitely not La Plata.

330
00:47:49.454 --> 00:47:51.656
Any ideas for the next assignment?

331
00:47:53.091 --> 00:47:55.727
I'm thinking. but nothing specific yet.

332
00:47:56.127 --> 00:47:58.726
Don't overthink it.
Get a camera from the storeroom.

333
00:47:58.796 --> 00:48:02.066
and go out and find something true.
from the real world.

334
00:48:05.636 --> 00:48:07.869
I have some time before the next class.

335
00:48:07.939 --> 00:48:09.707
Do you want to come to my office?

336
00:48:09.974 --> 00:48:12.810
Will you tell me your thoughts?
Can I help you?

337
00:48:16.748 --> 00:48:18.182
I can't. sorry.

338
00:50:28.980 --> 00:50:30.748
Excuse me. could you open the door?

339
00:50:31.849 --> 00:50:33.251
Could you open. please?

340
00:53:04.769 --> 00:53:08.272
<i>- Cami. are you having dinner with us?
- No. I have things to do.</i>

341
00:54:03.627 --> 00:54:08.132
CLAUDE MONTAND - 105 STREET. APT. 1885
LA PLATA. 1900

342
00:54:10.000 --> 00:54:12.803
MARIE MONTAND - 105 STREET. APT. 1885
LA PLATA. 1900

343
00:54:47.138 --> 00:54:48.739
Get out of the way!

344
00:55:39.256 --> 00:55:41.225
<i>Shut the fucking door!</i>

345
00:56:21.832 --> 00:56:27.605
MONTAND. CLAUDE
105 ST. - APT. 1885

346
00:56:35.946 --> 00:56:36.947
<i>Hello?</i>

347
00:56:38.716 --> 00:56:39.750
<i>Hello?</i>

348
00:56:42.987 --> 00:56:44.154
<i>Who is it?</i>

349
00:57:14.818 --> 00:57:17.284
DIRECTED BY CAMILA SEOANE

350
00:57:17.354 --> 00:57:19.089
Open them. Javier.

351
00:57:21.325 --> 00:57:22.459
Well...

352
00:57:23.294 --> 00:57:24.595
Who's going to start?

353
00:57:29.967 --> 00:57:31.402
No one?

354
00:57:35.472 --> 00:57:38.676
Cami. did this girl know
you were filming her?

355
00:57:39.977 --> 00:57:41.178
Of course.

356
00:57:43.013 --> 00:57:46.580
So what we saw. what was it?
It's a fiction.

357
00:57:46.650 --> 00:57:48.218
It's not a documentary. right?

358
00:57:48.886 --> 00:57:51.088
It's a strange piece.

359
00:57:51.956 --> 00:57:55.392
It's sad. but scary at the same time.

360
00:57:57.061 --> 00:57:58.562
I like it.

361
00:57:59.663 --> 00:58:01.231
It's not something usual.

362
00:58:03.300 --> 00:58:05.135
The bodyguard again.

363
00:58:06.570 --> 00:58:07.871
Anyone else?

364
00:58:11.675 --> 00:58:14.074
- Alright. who's next?
- Me. Cuevas.

365
00:58:14.144 --> 00:58:15.409
Go ahead.

366
00:58:15.479 --> 00:58:17.211
Today's assignment...

367
00:58:17.281 --> 00:58:19.817
Sorry. aren't you going to tell me
what you think?

368
00:58:20.451 --> 00:58:22.152
There's not much to say. Cami.

369
00:58:22.453 --> 00:58:24.518
If you want to talk. come by my office.

370
00:58:24.588 --> 00:58:26.320
I don't want to go to your office.

371
00:58:26.390 --> 00:58:29.159
I want your opinion.
I don't believe you didn't like it.

372
00:58:34.198 --> 00:58:36.897
It's the most amateur short
you've ever made.

373
00:58:36.967 --> 00:58:38.732
You broke all the rules.

374
00:58:38.802 --> 00:58:41.669
Maybe to look modern.
but it doesn't work.

375
00:58:41.739 --> 00:58:45.906
The out-of-focus shots don't work.
the supposed tension doesn't work

376
00:58:45.976 --> 00:58:48.809
and. of course.
the editing doesn't work.

377
00:58:48.879 --> 00:58:51.779
I didn't get it at all.
because it doesn't stir me one bit.

378
00:58:51.849 --> 00:58:55.185
It's exhibitionist and superficial.
I can go on.

379
00:58:59.523 --> 00:59:00.758
No need.

380
00:59:01.291 --> 00:59:02.426
Go ahead. Fede.

381
00:59:02.926 --> 00:59:07.031
My exercise was the quest for cinema
from a view of hatred.

382
00:59:13.370 --> 00:59:14.371
Cami.

383
00:59:15.773 --> 00:59:17.474
Something going on with Cuevas?

384
00:59:17.841 --> 00:59:18.976
No. nothing.

385
00:59:19.443 --> 00:59:21.345
Where'd you get that actress?

386
00:59:22.212 --> 00:59:23.414
She's a friend.

387
00:59:23.847 --> 00:59:26.013
I'd love to work with her.
she's amazing.

388
00:59:26.083 --> 00:59:28.649
She doesn't like working with strangers.

389
00:59:28.719 --> 00:59:32.322
- Introduce me to her.
- She's in France now. she's from there.

390
00:59:32.790 --> 00:59:34.224
When she gets back. maybe.

391
00:59:35.793 --> 00:59:37.725
Don't sweat it. he's a fascist.

392
00:59:37.795 --> 00:59:39.797
Let's go gave a drink. I'm buying.

393
00:59:40.064 --> 00:59:41.231
I don't feel like it.

394
00:59:43.100 --> 00:59:45.903
Better alone crying.
watching Polish movies. right?

395
00:59:47.071 --> 00:59:48.072
Wait.

396
00:59:51.175 --> 00:59:52.843
Did you really like the short?

397
01:00:09.393 --> 01:00:10.828
Where are you?

398
01:00:47.064 --> 01:00:50.234
Come on. girl.
you're not filming anything.

399
01:00:53.337 --> 01:00:55.439
Why don't you film this?

400
01:01:34.344 --> 01:01:40.350
FOR SALE

401
01:02:41.878 --> 01:02:42.980
What?

402
01:02:44.348 --> 01:02:46.683
I don't understand you.
What are you saying?

403
01:02:49.686 --> 01:02:52.122
Are you insane?
What are you talking about?

404
01:02:53.991 --> 01:02:56.827
What? You're crazy.
What are you talking about?

405
01:02:57.294 --> 01:02:58.929
Talk to me in Spanish.

406
01:05:57.874 --> 01:06:01.174
I'm also looking around
because I have a friend who wants to...

407
01:06:01.244 --> 01:06:03.176
An actor friend who wants to act.

408
01:06:03.246 --> 01:06:04.909
I don't know if I like the way he acts.

409
01:06:04.979 --> 01:06:08.008
I felt like doing something
about a couple or...

410
01:06:08.078 --> 01:06:09.583
I don't know.

411
01:06:09.653 --> 01:06:11.585
My friend. the actress in the short...

412
01:06:11.655 --> 01:06:12.786
- Yes?
- She's back.

413
01:06:12.856 --> 01:06:16.526
- If you want. I'll give you the number.
- You know I already met her?

414
01:06:19.529 --> 01:06:21.631
Yes. in Blast.

415
01:06:23.300 --> 01:06:25.969
What?
Blast. the club.

416
01:06:26.670 --> 01:06:29.369
You have to go out more.
You can't be a good director

417
01:06:29.439 --> 01:06:31.541
if all you do
is stay locked in your room.

418
01:06:32.108 --> 01:06:33.273
What is it? A bar?

419
01:06:33.343 --> 01:06:35.942
Yeah. a club. a big bar.

420
01:06:36.012 --> 01:06:38.078
And people dance. drink...

421
01:06:38.148 --> 01:06:40.617
Yes. I think I saw something
like that in a movie.

422
01:06:41.651 --> 01:06:44.618
- Yeah. well. it's better in person.
- You don't say.

423
01:06:44.688 --> 01:06:46.122
We can go later if you want.

424
01:06:47.691 --> 01:06:49.226
Fine. Is Marie going?

425
01:06:49.759 --> 01:06:51.928
What. are you jealous?

426
01:06:53.630 --> 01:06:54.798
Maybe.

427
01:06:57.767 --> 01:07:02.339
You could have warned me
that the chick was nuts.

428
01:07:03.740 --> 01:07:05.208
You ended up in her house?

429
01:07:09.446 --> 01:07:10.780
So you met the old man?

430
01:07:13.250 --> 01:07:14.584
We were alone.

431
01:07:16.286 --> 01:07:17.554
Are you sure?

432
01:07:19.189 --> 01:07:20.690
What she did tell me

433
01:07:21.124 --> 01:07:24.094
is she didn't care
about being an actress.

434
01:07:24.995 --> 01:07:27.197
I asked her about your short.

435
01:07:27.797 --> 01:07:29.065
She didn't even remember.

436
01:07:30.333 --> 01:07:31.468
That's strange.

437
01:07:34.371 --> 01:07:36.139
Don't worry. I didn't say anything.

438
01:07:36.706 --> 01:07:37.707
About what?

439
01:07:38.408 --> 01:07:41.845
- Her not knowing you were filming her.
- Of course she knows.

440
01:07:44.214 --> 01:07:48.018
She must've been super drunk.
so she doesn't remember.

441
01:07:48.818 --> 01:07:52.819
- She really likes beer.
- Also vodka. coke. pills...

442
01:07:52.889 --> 01:07:54.521
- Did you make a list?
- Guys.

443
01:07:54.591 --> 01:07:55.692
Guys?

444
01:07:56.760 --> 01:07:59.029
It seems she's banged half La Plata.

445
01:08:02.165 --> 01:08:03.700
And you the other half. right?

446
01:08:05.302 --> 01:08:06.369
That's right.

447
01:08:08.838 --> 01:08:10.974
But enough of the French girl.

448
01:08:11.575 --> 01:08:13.577
How are you?

449
01:08:14.311 --> 01:08:16.212
Same as always. You?

450
01:08:16.813 --> 01:08:18.148
Same as always.

451
01:08:19.916 --> 01:08:21.248
What's wrong with you?

452
01:08:21.318 --> 01:08:24.287
- What's wrong with you?
- Why the fuck did you bring me here?

453
01:08:25.121 --> 01:08:26.890
Are you into me or not?

454
01:09:11.968 --> 01:09:13.236
Hello.

455
01:09:15.271 --> 01:09:16.506
How are you?

456
01:09:43.967 --> 01:09:45.301
I know you.

457
01:09:46.970 --> 01:09:48.371
No. I don't think so.

458
01:09:56.346 --> 01:09:57.714
I feel like I do.

459
01:10:53.837 --> 01:10:56.372
- What the fuck?
- What's going on?

460
01:10:56.840 --> 01:10:58.074
Shit!

461
01:11:00.076 --> 01:11:02.078
What do you do in life. Camila?

462
01:11:02.545 --> 01:11:03.880
I study film.

463
01:11:05.749 --> 01:11:08.785
- To be an actress?
- No. a director.

464
01:11:11.588 --> 01:11:12.956
Are you good?

465
01:11:14.057 --> 01:11:17.127
I could be. but I have a long way to go.

466
01:11:18.962 --> 01:11:21.831
I met a guy who also studies film.

467
01:11:22.298 --> 01:11:25.935
Tall. handsome. shaved head...

468
01:11:26.803 --> 01:11:28.772
Do you know him?

469
01:11:30.073 --> 01:11:33.343
Better yet. he's kind of an asshole.

470
01:11:35.211 --> 01:11:37.080
And you. what do you do?

471
01:11:38.748 --> 01:11:40.383
I don't do anything.

472
01:11:54.063 --> 01:11:56.633
Interested in moving
to the neighborhood?

473
01:11:58.701 --> 01:12:01.004
You look at that building a lot.

474
01:12:03.039 --> 01:12:05.642
I don't know. it gives me a bad vibe.

475
01:12:07.977 --> 01:12:09.142
Have you ever thought

476
01:12:09.212 --> 01:12:12.779
of sneaking into an empty place
and hiding from everyone?

477
01:12:12.849 --> 01:12:13.983
FOR SALE

478
01:12:36.272 --> 01:12:37.607
Do you have a boyfriend?

479
01:12:38.942 --> 01:12:40.610
No. thank you.

480
01:12:41.778 --> 01:12:43.346
Well. you must have someone.

481
01:12:44.814 --> 01:12:46.249
And you?

482
01:12:49.485 --> 01:12:53.122
But I would tell you.
especially if he was bad for me.

483
01:12:55.024 --> 01:12:56.759
Do you want to tell me something?

484
01:13:03.066 --> 01:13:04.634
What are we doing tomorrow?

485
01:13:06.202 --> 01:13:09.539
Take me to a new club I don't know.

486
01:13:10.807 --> 01:13:12.609
We can go to the movies.

487
01:13:17.113 --> 01:13:18.414
Okay.

488
01:13:22.719 --> 01:13:25.088
And your parents. where are they?

489
01:13:28.524 --> 01:13:31.594
China. Chile. Cyprus...

490
01:13:33.429 --> 01:13:34.764
My...

491
01:13:35.298 --> 01:13:38.368
My old man is an idiot.

492
01:13:38.868 --> 01:13:40.737
He's stupid...

493
01:13:42.038 --> 01:13:44.107
I don't care about my old man.

494
01:14:09.465 --> 01:14:11.267
Please don't go.

495
01:14:12.135 --> 01:14:14.170
There's a T-shirt over there.

496
01:14:48.404 --> 01:14:49.405
Camila.

497
01:14:51.874 --> 01:14:52.875
What?

498
01:14:55.178 --> 01:14:57.447
I think I'm going crazy.

499
01:15:01.250 --> 01:15:02.618
No. don't say that.

500
01:15:04.554 --> 01:15:05.688
It's true.

501
01:15:07.724 --> 01:15:09.258
We're cursed.

502
01:15:13.329 --> 01:15:14.564
Us?

503
01:15:24.841 --> 01:15:26.142
I'll take care of you.

504
01:16:49.358 --> 01:16:52.261
PREGNANCY TEST

505
01:17:13.950 --> 01:17:15.151
Hello.

506
01:17:15.852 --> 01:17:16.886
Hello.

507
01:17:22.225 --> 01:17:24.127
I'm Camila. a friend.

508
01:17:27.029 --> 01:17:28.431
Do you know where Marie is?

509
01:17:29.532 --> 01:17:31.034
She said she'd be right back.

510
01:17:32.902 --> 01:17:35.538
Lisbeth. go play in the garden.

511
01:17:43.613 --> 01:17:44.914
Get dressed.

512
01:17:46.015 --> 01:17:47.183
Yes. sorry.

513
01:17:56.559 --> 01:17:58.561
Did she say where she was going?

514
01:18:03.299 --> 01:18:05.898
She's supposed to be
looking after her sister today.

515
01:18:05.968 --> 01:18:08.838
but once again
she shirks her responsibility.

516
01:18:12.141 --> 01:18:14.810
Marie loves Lisbeth very much.

517
01:18:18.147 --> 01:18:19.482
How do you think she is?

518
01:18:21.250 --> 01:18:22.385
She seems better.

519
01:18:25.054 --> 01:18:26.622
Marie needs help.

520
01:18:28.424 --> 01:18:30.092
I can help her.

521
01:18:30.893 --> 01:18:32.528
Professional help.

522
01:18:35.298 --> 01:18:37.166
What do you think is wrong with her?

523
01:18:39.635 --> 01:18:42.171
I'm starting to think
it's the same as her mother.

524
01:18:45.041 --> 01:18:46.842
And what's wrong with your mother?

525
01:18:52.481 --> 01:18:54.283
She always avoids the subject.

526
01:18:56.852 --> 01:18:59.855
That's private. a family matter.

527
01:19:03.292 --> 01:19:04.924
Well. when you see her.

528
01:19:04.994 --> 01:19:07.797
tell her I've taken care of Lisbeth.

529
01:19:08.698 --> 01:19:10.900
Or even better. don't tell her anything.

530
01:19:11.834 --> 01:19:13.603
You can see yourself out. right?

531
01:20:42.224 --> 01:20:43.689
- Hi.
- Hi.

532
01:20:43.759 --> 01:20:45.594
- Are you busy?
- What happened to you?

533
01:20:46.062 --> 01:20:48.227
Nothing.
Did you want to go to the movies?

534
01:20:48.297 --> 01:20:49.632
What do you mean nothing?

535
01:20:50.266 --> 01:20:52.968
- Come on. let's go to the movies.
- Who did that to you?

536
01:20:55.137 --> 01:20:56.869
- I don't know.
- Yes. you know.

537
01:20:56.939 --> 01:20:59.075
Why are you with that guy?
Who is he?

538
01:20:59.542 --> 01:21:00.543
What guy?

539
01:21:02.445 --> 01:21:04.910
Camila. please wait.

540
01:21:04.980 --> 01:21:06.282
Camila. stop.

541
01:21:09.819 --> 01:21:12.655
Is Adolfo the father?
Or is it the old man's?

542
01:21:13.723 --> 01:21:14.990
How do you know that?

543
01:21:17.159 --> 01:21:20.663
- I hope it's not the old man.
- What? What old man?

544
01:21:21.630 --> 01:21:23.766
The one who's with you all the time.

545
01:21:24.633 --> 01:21:26.035
What are you taking about?

546
01:21:28.771 --> 01:21:29.772
Come.

547
01:21:34.543 --> 01:21:35.878
Over here.

548
01:21:37.113 --> 01:21:39.348
<i>- Cami. honey...?
- We're in my room.</i>

549
01:22:17.653 --> 01:22:18.788
What is this?

550
01:22:29.465 --> 01:22:32.064
Fucking pervert. What is this?

551
01:22:32.134 --> 01:22:34.066
- Hold on.
- No. You're gross.

552
01:22:34.136 --> 01:22:35.868
- Turn that off!
- Just one second.

553
01:22:35.938 --> 01:22:37.907
- Turn that off!
- Look. Look.

554
01:22:54.023 --> 01:22:55.057
It's him. isn't it?

555
01:22:57.092 --> 01:22:58.360
Did he hit you?

556
01:23:01.363 --> 01:23:02.698
I don't know.

557
01:23:04.333 --> 01:23:05.634
Let's go to the police.

558
01:23:06.802 --> 01:23:07.937
Come on.

559
01:23:12.575 --> 01:23:13.843
I was all alone.

560
01:23:18.814 --> 01:23:19.949
I was alone.

561
01:24:33.322 --> 01:24:35.991
Hello. Are you Cami's friend?

562
01:24:37.293 --> 01:24:38.527
Are you okay?

563
01:24:40.396 --> 01:24:42.464
Let me see you. What happened to you?

564
01:24:45.134 --> 01:24:46.569
What happened?

565
01:24:49.338 --> 01:24:51.006
What's wrong. sweetheart?

566
01:24:53.208 --> 01:24:56.011
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

567
01:24:56.345 --> 01:24:58.210
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

568
01:24:58.280 --> 01:24:59.915
What did you do? What happened?

569
01:25:17.700 --> 01:25:19.668
What happened? Come here.

570
01:26:25.834 --> 01:26:26.935
It's here?

571
01:26:29.038 --> 01:26:32.374
No. further down. Over there.

572
01:27:31.533 --> 01:27:32.968
<i>- Hello?
- Lisbeth?</i>

573
01:27:33.869 --> 01:27:36.405
<i>- It's me.
- What happened to you?</i>

574
01:27:36.739 --> 01:27:38.073
Nothing happened to me.

575
01:27:38.874 --> 01:27:40.342
I have to tell you something.

576
01:27:40.776 --> 01:27:42.344
You have to listen to me. okay?

577
01:27:42.811 --> 01:27:43.946
<i>Okay.</i>

578
01:27:44.446 --> 01:27:47.883
From now on you have to be very careful.

579
01:27:49.918 --> 01:27:50.916
Okay? I...

580
01:27:50.986 --> 01:27:52.851
<i>Give me the phone. Go to your room.</i>

581
01:27:52.921 --> 01:27:55.057
<i>- Marie. where are you?
- Dad.</i>

582
01:27:55.657 --> 01:27:58.757
<i>- Honey. listen...
- Dad. I have to tell you something.</i>

583
01:27:58.827 --> 01:28:01.827
<i>Honey. please come home right away.</i>

584
01:28:01.897 --> 01:28:05.464
Dad. I have to tell you something.
It's very difficult. Please listen.

585
01:28:05.534 --> 01:28:06.999
Listen to me for real.

586
01:28:07.069 --> 01:28:09.668
<i>They say you hurt a girl very badly.
your friend.</i>

587
01:28:09.738 --> 01:28:11.840
<i>I don't understand.
Tell me what happened.</i>

588
01:28:12.407 --> 01:28:13.839
It wasn't me.

589
01:28:13.909 --> 01:28:17.246
<i>The police say they found your bag
in her house. in her room.</i>

590
01:28:19.181 --> 01:28:20.779
It wasn't me. it was him.

591
01:28:20.849 --> 01:28:24.119
<i>- Wait. Him? Who. Marie?
- I don't know who he is.</i>

592
01:28:24.853 --> 01:28:26.321
<i>Honey. you're scaring me.</i>

593
01:28:28.957 --> 01:28:29.955
<i>You scare me.</i>

594
01:28:30.025 --> 01:28:33.392
<i>Please tell me where you are
and I'll pick you up.</i>

595
01:28:33.462 --> 01:28:35.798
I'm going to tell you.
But listen to me. okay?

596
01:28:37.833 --> 01:28:39.468
<i>Go ahead. I'm listening.</i>

597
01:28:43.739 --> 01:28:47.606
It's a man. an old man.
You can't see him. but you can film him.

598
01:28:47.676 --> 01:28:49.007
<i>What are you telling me?</i>

599
01:28:49.077 --> 01:28:52.044
I know. But he's always with me
and he was with Mom.

600
01:28:52.114 --> 01:28:53.746
Mom died because of him.

601
01:28:53.816 --> 01:28:55.948
He started coming with me when Mom died.

602
01:28:56.018 --> 01:28:59.118
<i>What are you telling me?
Marie. what man?</i>

603
01:28:59.188 --> 01:29:00.222
I don't know.

604
01:29:01.390 --> 01:29:03.525
But that's why Mom died.

605
01:29:03.859 --> 01:29:05.961
<i>Honey. no. You're in shock.</i>

606
01:29:07.062 --> 01:29:08.997
<i>Come home and tell me what happened.</i>

607
01:29:09.798 --> 01:29:11.630
Mom left to protect us from him.

608
01:29:11.700 --> 01:29:15.510
<i>No. Marie. your mother...
killed herself.</i>

609
01:29:15.880 --> 01:29:17.404
- No!
- <i>She wasn't well.</i>

610
01:29:17.474 --> 01:29:19.375
<i>She left home and killed herself.</i>

611
01:29:21.844 --> 01:29:22.878
Don't say that.

612
01:29:23.345 --> 01:29:24.413
<i>I can't take anymore.</i>

613
01:29:25.480 --> 01:29:26.745
<i>I can't handle this.</i>

614
01:29:26.815 --> 01:29:27.816
Dad...

615
01:29:32.821 --> 01:29:35.487
Dad. think what you want about me.

616
01:29:35.557 --> 01:29:37.656
but you have to take
good care of Lisbeth.

617
01:29:37.726 --> 01:29:39.127
<i>- Don't talk about her.
- Okay?</i>

618
01:29:39.728 --> 01:29:42.998
<i>- I'm scared he'll come after her.
- Your sister won't be like you.</i>

619
01:29:48.570 --> 01:29:49.905
Put her on the phone.

620
01:29:50.939 --> 01:29:52.741
<i>You're not speaking to your sister.</i>

621
01:29:54.176 --> 01:29:56.645
Please. I want speak to her.

622
01:29:58.547 --> 01:30:01.516
<i>Leave your sister alone.
that's all I ask of you.</i>

623
01:30:04.419 --> 01:30:07.589
I'll call you back. okay?
I'll explain it all better.

624
01:30:09.157 --> 01:30:12.461
<i>No. come home. Marie. You need help.</i>

625
01:30:12.861 --> 01:30:14.626
<i>I'm begging you. come home.</i>

626
01:30:14.696 --> 01:30:17.296
<i>- Take care of Lisbeth.
- Marie. tell me where you are.</i>

627
01:30:17.366 --> 01:30:19.264
<i>- Take care.
- Honey. don't go.</i>

628
01:30:19.334 --> 01:30:21.370
<i>- Okay?
- Honey. please don't hang up.</i>

629
01:30:21.637 --> 01:30:23.168
<i>- Marie. please!
- Goodbye.</i>

630
01:30:23.238 --> 01:30:24.806
<i>Mary. Mary!</i>

631
01:30:44.459 --> 01:30:47.429
FOR SALE

632
01:31:54.296 --> 01:32:00.302
FOR SALE

633
01:35:35.700 --> 01:35:36.715
Mom.

634
01:35:36.785 --> 01:35:37.819
Mom!

635
01:35:38.000 --> 01:35:39.000
Mom!

636
01:37:08.143 --> 01:37:09.210
Open up!

637
01:37:10.312 --> 01:37:11.843
Son of a bitch!

638
01:37:11.913 --> 01:37:14.145
Open up!

639
01:37:14.215 --> 01:37:15.180
Open it!

640
01:37:15.250 --> 01:37:16.351
Mom!

641
01:37:27.095 --> 01:37:28.059
There she is.

642
01:37:28.129 --> 01:37:30.165
Mom. I'll get you out of there!

643
01:37:32.834 --> 01:37:35.203
Hold on. Hold on.

644
01:37:35.570 --> 01:37:37.305
Let's see this. Let go!

645
01:37:37.939 --> 01:37:39.170
Let go!

646
01:37:39.240 --> 01:37:41.072
Let go. Stay still.

647
01:37:41.142 --> 01:37:42.374
Mom!

648
01:37:42.444 --> 01:37:43.945
Come on.

649
01:37:44.546 --> 01:37:45.547
Open.

650
01:37:46.081 --> 01:37:47.112
Get in.

651
01:37:47.182 --> 01:37:50.518
Get in. Get in. Get in. Get in!

652
01:38:48.009 --> 01:38:50.745
<i>Hello. Lisbeth. It's Mercedes.</i>

653
01:38:52.080 --> 01:38:55.013
<i>I'm calling to tell you that. finally.</i>

654
01:38:55.083 --> 01:38:56.718
<i>Sara's coming too.</i>

655
01:38:57.018 --> 01:38:58.953
<i>She's a friend of Andrea's.</i>

656
01:39:00.588 --> 01:39:02.590
<i>I was with her when she died...</i>

657
01:39:04.559 --> 01:39:06.561
<i>And she wants to talk to you too.</i>

658
01:39:07.729 --> 01:39:11.232
<i>Thank you again for letting us
go to meet you.</i>

659
01:39:12.133 --> 01:39:16.204
<i>I really think this is important
for understanding</i>

660
01:39:16.538 --> 01:39:19.874
<i>what happened to your sister
and my daughter</i>

661
01:39:20.408 --> 01:39:24.212
<i>because. when Andrea
told us all about it.</i>

662
01:39:24.879 --> 01:39:26.815
<i>we couldn't believe her.</i>

663
01:39:27.582 --> 01:39:29.050
<i>Or we didn't want to.</i>

664
01:39:30.118 --> 01:39:33.421
<i>But now we realize that it was all true.</i>

665
01:39:34.289 --> 01:39:37.859
<i>I hope this helps us all.</i>

666
01:40:02.917 --> 01:40:05.386
I think that's
what's happening to me now.

667
01:40:08.389 --> 01:40:09.424
To you?

668
01:40:16.297 --> 01:40:17.532
Don't worry.

669
01:40:19.901 --> 01:40:21.135
We're here.

670
01:40:42.156 --> 01:40:47.161
LISBETH BRUSELAS. 2023

671
01:42:05.340 --> 01:42:09.310
THE WAILING
